==Swedish==
====Etymology====
The word is originally a short form for ''Tyrs dag'' (day of [[w:Tyr|Tyr]]).

===Noun===
'''tisdag''' ''c'' (''plural'' [[tisdagar]], ''definite singular'' [[tisdagen]], ''definite plural'' [[tisdagarna]], ''genitive singular'' [[tisdags]], ''genitive singular definite'' [[tisdagens]], ''genitive plural'' [[tisdagars]], ''genitive plural definite'' [[tisdagarnas]])

# [[Tuesday]]. The second day of the [[week]] (according to the [[ISO]] 8601 [[standard]]).

